Component not found for symbol %s at %s, reuse id %d."
Msg.ExtDesc:
Logic synchronization warnings are typically due to having one or more Reuse blocks in the schematic where you may have performed Reuse annotation by which the old Reuse ID has been overwritten by new a one. Due to mismatch REUSE_IDs, you get this warning when placing the mdd file into the physical editor.
While in the schematic (DE-HDL) while in the sub-design flow, when you copy/paste of components within the pages of the design, the Packager re-assigns the REUSE_ID for the components when you perform Export Physical, this results in the warning in Allegro. The REUSE_ID property is automatically attached to a component, it allows for the correct assignment of logic within a module instance. The REUSE_ID property is a number that uniquely identifies each symbol and component within a module. It is used to re-connect reference designators when a module is used in the physical design, thus allowing for the correct assignment of logic within a module instance. The property is stored within the module file (mdd) and the board design file that represents the module information, and it is back annotated to the schematic that represents the module's logic.
Because this property is for Cadence internal use only, do not edit it.
To remove this warning message, go to File> Export Physical> Advanced. Next select sub design tab and remove the sub design generation option.
Once the Sub Design has been packaged using the Generate Subdesign mode and associated with interim board and the module is created, the DE-HDL Subdesign and module are in sync.
This process assigns REUSE_ID's in DE-HDL and they are passed to Allegro.
At this stage, the SubDesign and module should be put in libraries with READ ONLY privileges.
Note: If further packaging passes are made using Generate Subdesign, the REUSE_ID's are all reassigned and the module (mdd) will no longer be in sync. In this event, you would be required to recreate the module.
Do not these warnings.

In-line help documentation for shape autovoiding form's thru pin clearance fields.
Msg.ExtDesc:
If set to DRC, shape voiding uses constraint-derived thru pin to shape spacing value as clearance. This clearance value is based on the specific and prioritized spacing value, which is determined by net, region, and constraint set memberships.
If set to Thermal/anti, shape voiding uses the size of thermal relief or anti pad defined on the shape layer as clearance. By default, no additional clearance is defined relative to this value. For extra clearance, specify the Oversize value. If the anti pad doesn't provide adequate clearance between the shape and the regular pad, DRCs will result and will not be cleared.
To increase clearance for all thru pins against which this shape is voided, set the Oversize value. To apply an oversize only on a single pin, add the DYN_CLEARANCE_OVERSIZE_ARRAY property to the pin on the required layers.
The DYN_CLEARANCE_TYPE property can also be used to override the clearance type (DRC, thermal/anti, or none) at the object level. A value of none means no voiding is done at all relative to the object and may result in DRCs.

Msg.Desc: In-line help documentation for shape autovoiding form's smd pin clearance fields.
Msg.ExtDesc:
If set to DRC, shape voiding uses constraint-derived SMD pin to shape spacing value as clearance. This clearance value is based on the specific and prioritized spacing value, which is determined by net, region, and constraint set memberships.
If set to Thermal/anti, shape voiding uses the size of thermal relief or anti pad defined on the shape layer as clearance. By default, no additional clearance is defined relative to this value. For extra clearance, specify the Oversize value. If the anti pad doesn't provide adequate clearance between the shape and the regular pad, DRCs will result and will not be cleared.
To increase clearance for all SMD pins against which this shape is voided, set the Oversize value. To apply an oversize only on a single pin, add the DYN_CLEARANCE_OVERSIZE_ARRAY property to the pin on the required layers.
The DYN_CLEARANCE_TYPE property can also be used to override the clearance type (DRC, thermal/anti, or none) at the object level. A value of none means no voiding is done at all relative to the object and may result in DRCs.

Msg.Desc: In-line help documentation for shape autovoiding form's via clearance fields.
Msg.ExtDesc:
If set to DRC, shape voiding uses constraint-derived via to shape spacing value as clearance. This clearance value is based on the specific and prioritized spacing value, which is determined by net, region, and constraint set memberships.
If set to Thermal/anti, shape voiding uses the size of thermal relief or anti pad defined on the shape layer as clearance. By default, no additional clearance is defined relative to this value. For extra clearance, specify the Oversize value. If the anti pad doesn't provide adequate clearance between the shape and the regular pad, DRCs will result and will not be cleared.
To increase clearance for all vias against which this shape is voided, set the Oversize value. To apply an oversize only on a single via, add the DYN_CLEARANCE_OVERSIZE_ARRAY property to the via on the required layers.
The DYN_CLEARANCE_TYPE property can also be used to override the clearance type (DRC, thermal/anti, or none) at the object level. A value of none means no voiding is done at all relative to the object and may result in DRCs.
NOTE: Applies to all types of vias in the design.

Msg.Desc: In-line help documentation for shape autovoiding form's line clearance fields.
Msg.ExtDesc:
Shape voiding clearance to traces is always done based on the specific and prioritized spacing value, which is determined by net, region, and constraint set memberships.
To increase clearance for all traces against which this shape is voided, set the Oversize value. To apply an oversize only on a single cline, add the DYN_CLEARANCE_OVERSIZE_ARRAY property to the cline.

Msg.Desc: In-line help documentation for shape autovoiding form's text clearance fields.
Msg.ExtDesc:
Shape voiding clearance to text is always done based on the specific and prioritized spacing value, which is determined by net, region, and constraint set memberships. Text does not have its own object type in Constraint Manager, and is governed by the cline to shape rules.
To increase clearance for all texts against which this shape is voided, set the Oversize value. Text voiding oversize may not be applied to individual text objects in the database.

Msg.Desc: In-line help documentation for shape autovoiding form's shape clearance fields.
Msg.ExtDesc:
Shape voiding clearance to other shapes is always done based on the specific and prioritized spacing value, which is determined by net, region, and constraint set memberships.
To increase clearance for all shapes against which this shape is voided, set the Oversize value. To apply an oversize only on a single shape, add the DYN_CLEARANCE_OVERSIZE_ARRAY property to the shape.
